%N A221440 Number of n X 2 binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1.
%H A221440 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A221440/b221440.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A221440 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,1,1).
%F A221440 Empirical: a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + a(n-2) + a(n-3).
%F A221440 Empirical g.f.: x*(3 + x^2) / (1 - 3*x - x^2 - x^3). - _Colin Barker_, Aug 05 2018
%F A221440 The above empirical formulas confirmed using the transfer matrix method. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 16 2026
%e A221440 Some solutions for n=3:
